Mix dressing, mustard, steak sauce and pepper in shallow dish. Add steak; turn to evenly coat both sides. Let stand 15 minutes to marinate, turning occasionally. Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade. Place steak on rack of broiler pan. Broil, 6 inches from heat source, 4 minutes on each side or to medium doneness (160 degrees F). Let stand 5 minutes before cutting across the grain into thin slices to serve.